The paper deals with secure computation and privacy-preserving aggregation, which are topics typically studied in the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of anonymous messages and the focus on reducing communication suggest that cs.CR and cs.DS are the most likely categories, followed by cs.IT and cs.LG. The mention of differential privacy also suggests cs.SI as a possible category.
